10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Mem is best suited for researchers, writers, knowledge workers, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Smartsheet, meanwhile, shines for PMOs, construction, enterprise operations, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2020, Mem describes itself as \"AI-powered note-taking app that self-organizes and surfaces relevant information.\" Smartsheet, established in 2005, positions itself as \"Spreadsheet-based work management platform with AI automation for enterprises.\" With 15 years between them, Smartsheet brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Mem offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Smartsheet** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 4). However, this does not mean Mem is a poor choice — far from it. Mem excels in its own right, particularly for researchers and writers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value familiar spreadsheet interface, go with Smartsheet. If ai automatically organizes your notes matters more to you, Mem is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
